<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Mitigation Strategies</title>

    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css">
     <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Urbanist:wght@200;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.2/css/all.min.css" integrity="sha512-z3gLpd7yknf1YoNbCzqRKc4qyor8gaKU1qmn+CShxbuBusANI9QpRohGBreCFkKxLhei6S9CQXFEbbKuqLg0DA==" crossorigin="anonymous" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" />

    <!-- Custom Styles -->
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            color: #495057;
            font-family: urbanist;
        }

        .container {
            margin-top: 50px;

        }

        .strategy-container {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            
        }

        .strategy-title {
            cursor: pointer;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #a4c3b2;;
            color: #fff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .strategy-content {
            display: none;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border: 1px solid #007bff;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        h1 {
        padding: 5%;
        color: white;
        }

        .header {
            background-color: #193631;
           
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="header">
        <h1 class="text-center">Pest and Disease Mitigation Strategies</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy1')">Crop Rotation</div>
            <div id="strategy1" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Rotate different crops in a field over successive seasons to disrupt the life cycle of specific pests and diseases.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy2')">Companion Planting</div>
            <div id="strategy2" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Planting certain crops together to enhgance growth and deter pests.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy3')">Biological Control</div>
            <div id="strategy3" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Introduce natural predators and parasites, or pathogens to control pest populations. This can include releasing beneficial insects or using microbial pesticides.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy4')">Use of Resistant Varieties</div>
            <div id="strategy4" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Plant crop varieties that are resistant or tolerant to specific pests or diseases. This can reduce the need for chemical interventions.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy5')">Integrated Pest Management</div>
            <div id="strategy5" class="strategy-content">
                <p>A holistic approach that combines various strategies, including biological control, cultural practices, and judicious use of pesticides, to manage pests and diseases sustainably.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy6')">Proper Crop Spacing</div>
            <div id="strategy6" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Ensure appropriate spacing between plants to improve air circulationand reduce the spread of diseases.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy7')">Sanitation Practices</div>
            <div id="strategy7" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Remove and destroy infected plants or plant parts to prevent the spread of disases. Proper disposal of crop residues can also reduce overwintering sites for pests.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy8')">Trap Crops</div>
            <div id="strategy8" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Planting specific crops to attract pests away from the main crop. This helps in concentrating pests in a particular area for easier control.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy9')">Monitoring and Early Detection</div>
            <div id="strategy9" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Regularly inspect crops for signs of pests or diseases. Early detection allows for prompt action, reducing the severity of infestations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy10')">Mulching</div>
            <div id="strategy10" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Apply mulch to the soil surface to suppress weeds and create a barrier against soil-borne diseases.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy11')">Cultural Practices</div>
            <div id="strategy11" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Adjust planting dates, use of cover crops and other cultural practices to create conditions less favourable for pests and diseases.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy12')">Weather Monitoring</div>
            <div id="strategy12" class="strategy-content">
                <p>Consider weather patterns and forecasts when planning pest and disease management strategies. Certain weather conditions can favour the development and spread of pests and diseases.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="strategy-container">
            <div class="strategy-title" onclick="toggleContent('strategy13')">Use of Pesticides as a Last Resort</div>
            <div id="strategy13" class="strategy-content">
                <p>If necessary use pesticides judiciously and follow recommended application guidelines. Overuse can lead to resistance and negative environmental impacts.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bootstrap JS and jQuery -->
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.2.1.slim.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.12.9/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

    <!-- Custom JavaScript -->
    <script>
        function toggleContent(strategyId) {
            var content = document.getElementById(strategyId);
            if (content.style.display === "none" || content.style.display === "") {
                content.style.display = "block";
            } else {
                content.style.display = "none";
            }
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
